  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Crucially, as manually collecting force annotations from natural videos is both costly and difficult, we instead leverage physics simulators (e.g., Blender) to hand-craft perfectly annotated training data.",
    "With our data creation pipeline, we specify a collection of objects along with the force conditions, and simulate the resulting dynamics to obtain the paired training videos.",
    "We hypothesize that such sim2real generalization is feasible because state-of-the-art video generation models already encode strong priors about visual dynamics, and our paired force-video data serves the role of eliciting their understanding of the physics-based control signals.",
    "We implement Force Prompting by introducing additional force control as local or global vector fields on a video generation model (Yang et al., 2024) conditioned on initial frame and text.",
    "We also curate an evaluation benchmark of diverse objects and motion types to evaluate global and local force prompts."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
